Hologram figure mesh — public/holo/figure.glb
=============================================

Source model: "Superhero Male" (ubc-superhero-male.glb) from the Universal
Base Characters kit (standard FREE version) by Quaternius.

Source URLs:
- https://quaternius.com  (kit download page)
- https://www.patreon.com/quaternius  (author)

License: CC0 1.0 Universal (Public Domain Dedication)
https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/
The model is dedicated to the public domain; no attribution is required
(given here anyway with thanks).

The license file bundled with the kit (UBC-License_Standard.txt) states:

    License:
    CC0 1.0 Universal (CC0 1.0)
    Public Domain Dedication
    https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/

    Models by @Quaternius

figure.glb is a preprocessed derivative of that model (gltf-transform): only
the main body mesh is kept (face/eye detail meshes removed); animations,
skinning, materials, and all vertex attributes except POSITION/NORMAL are
stripped; node transforms are flattened and unused resources pruned. The
derivative remains CC0.

The shipped figure.glb is additionally re-posed (arms-down) and re-baked from the same CC0 asset's A-pose skeleton — no license change; bake scripts and probe reports live in the project provenance (holo-model/bake-armsdown.mjs).
